wikipedia_page.main: Sir Michael John Austin Cummins (26 November 1939 – 25 January 2020) was a British parliamentary official. He was the Serjeant-at-Arms of the British House of Commons between 2000 and 2005. He was knighted in the 2003 Birthday Honours.
